Cross-validation

valSet <- sample(1:ncol(expr.filt),157) #1/3 of data as validation set.
alphas <- seq(0,1,0.1)

cvout <- foreach(a=1:length(alphas),.combine='rbind') %dopar% {
  foreach(i=1:10,.combine='rbind') %dopar% {
    testSet <- sample(setdiff(1:ncol(expr.filt),valSet),58) #split the data again to a test subset
    testAndValid <- append(testSet,valSet)
    trainSet <- setdiff(1:ncol(expr.filt),testAndValid)

    fit <- glmnet(t(expr.filt[,trainSet]),subs$prediction[trainSet],family = "multinomial",alpha = alphas[a])
    preds <- predict(fit,t(expr.filt[,testSet]),type="response")

    foreach(j=1:dim(preds)[[3]],.combine = rbind) %dopar% {
      scores<-as.data.frame(preds[,,j])
      len<-length(which(levels(subs$prediction)[apply(scores[,c(1,2,3)],1,which.max)] == subs$prediction[testSet]))
      data.frame(i,fit$lambda[j],sum(fit$beta$Immune[,j]!=0),sum(fit$beta$Keratin[,j]!=0),sum(fit$beta$`MITF-low`[,j]!=0),len,alphas[a])
    }
  }
}






ggplot(cvout,aes(x=fit.lambda.j.,y=len/58)) + stat_smooth(level=0.99,span=0.4) + scale_x_continuous("Lambda") + scale_y_continuous("Prop identified correctly") + facet_wrap(~alphas.a.,ncol=3,scales="free_x") + geom_hline(yintercept = 0.9,color="red") + theme_classic()

y<- c()

for(i in unique(cvout$alphas.a.)){
  x <- cvout[which(cvout$alphas.a.==i),]
  y <- rbind(y,x[which.max(x$len/58),])
}
